### Description

Hello dear Angular devs,

Thanks for doing great work!

I have an issue that occurs whenever I want to update just the queryParams on a route and trigger a router event.
When the queryParams array gets additions and when I trigger a `router.navigate` event it won't update the queryParams unless I copy the array by value first, then it works as expected.

I assume this is a bug because the behavior is quite weird, I haven't found it documented anywhere and it took me a long time to find this out.

```
async updateQueryParam() {
    let routeQP: string | string[] =
      this.route.snapshot.queryParams['qp'] ?? [];
    if (routeQP instanceof Array === false) routeQP = [routeQP as string];
    // If the below is not added, query params will not always change with navigation
    //routeQP = [...routeQP];

    (routeQP as string[]).push(`Param ${this.count}`);
    this.count += 1;

    console.log('New params', routeQP);
    this.router.navigate([], {
      relativeTo: this.route,
      queryParams: {
        qp: routeQP.length > 0 ? routeQP : undefined,
      },
      queryParamsHandling: 'merge',
      //skipLocationChange: true
    });
```

If you uncomment the `routeQP = [...routeQP];` line, it works as expected and if you leave the comment there the router won't trigger an update.

The stackblitz doesn't seem to work for some reason, but you may download the example or copy the simple example to a new app and you may see the issue reproduced.

