### Description

After migrating from Angular 13 to Angular 14 and 15, I got some strange error on navigating to dynamic lazy loaded module. Error states that this route doesn't have loadChildren when, in fact, it has loadChildren pointing to a lazy loaded module. Also there is no named outlet anywhere in the app. This code worked on Angular 13, but broke after update to 14 and 15.



Definition of routes from EventRoutingModule:

```
const routes: Routes = [
  {
    path: "",
    component: ModeratorComponent,
    children: [
      {
        path: "",
        pathMatch: "full",
        redirectTo: "event-list",
      },
      {
        path: "event-list",
        loadChildren: () =>
          import("./event-list/event-list.module").then(
            (m) => m.EventListModule
          ),
      },
      {
        path: "event/loading",
        component: EventLoadingComponent,
      },
      {
        path: "event/:eventId",
        loadChildren: () =>
          import("./event/event.module").then((m) => m.EventModule),
        canActivate: [EventStoreGuard],
        canDeactivate: [EventStoreGuard],
      },
      {
        path: "admin",
        loadChildren: () =>
          import("@moderator/admin/admin.module").then((m) => m.AdminModule),
        canLoad: [AdminGuard],
      },
    ],
  },
  {
    path: "help",
    component: ModeratorHelpComponent,
  },
];
```

